# React & JSX Conventions

## Components

- Use **functional components** with `export default`
- One component per file; filename in **PascalCase** (e.g. `HeroSection.jsx`)

## Auth & Protected Routes

- Use `useAuth()` from `src/context/AuthContext.jsx` for user state
- Wrap student routes with `ProtectedRoute` for auth gating
- Do not call Firebase directly in UI; use `AuthContext` / `useAuth`

## Patterns

- Use `useMemo` for context values to avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Put reusable logic in custom hooks under `src/hooks/`
- Icons from `lucide-react`; animations from `framer-motion`

## Example

```jsx
// BAD: Class component, inline auth
class MyComponent extends React.Component { ... }

// GOOD: Functional component, useAuth
function MyComponent() {
  const { user, isAuthenticated } = useAuth();
  return <div>...</div>;
}
export default MyComponent;
```
